The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama marking April 2009 as National Cancer Control Month. It highlights the progress made in understanding, preventing, detecting, and treating cancer, but also acknowledges that cancer continues to be a leading cause of death in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of medical research and calls for increased support for research institutions. It also encourages individuals to take steps to decrease their risk of developing cancer, such as seeking regular check-ups, engaging in healthy habits, and moderating alcohol intake and sun exposure. The proclamation concludes by calling for collaboration among cancer patients, survivors, healthcare providers, researchers, advocates, and others to work together to control and defeat cancer.